{"word":"H5553 - סֶלַע - çelaʻ - seh'-lah - Rock","slug":"H5553","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סֶלַע</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çelaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>seh'-lah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Rock"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E1;&#x05DC;&#x05E2; - sela&#x201B;</b> - <i>seh'-lah</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to be <i>lofty</i>; a craggy <i>rock</i>, literally or figuratively (a <i>fortress</i>): - (ragged) rock, stone (-ny), strong hold."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5554\">H5554</a>, <a href=\"#/H5556\">H5556</a>"}]}